In [39]:
def qc_prob(alpha):
    qc = QuantumCircuit(1,1) 
    initial_state = [np.sqrt(alpha),np.sqrt(1-alpha)]
    qc.initialize(initial_state, 0) 
    qc.measure(0,0)
    return qc
In [41]:
qc = qc_prob(0.14)
qobj = assemble(qc,shots=1000)
results = backend.run(qobj).result().get_counts()
plot_histogram(results)

2. Bloch Sphere¶

  • Amplitude .
  • $0.5 = \mid \alpha \mid^2$ $\alpha$ .

  • $\alpha = \sqrt{0.5}e^{i \theta}$ $\theta$ .

  • $\mathbb{C}^2$ $\mathbb{R}^4$ Global Phase Invariance 3 $\bra{\psi}\ket{\psi}=1$ .

  • Bloch Shere .

$$\ket{\psi} = \cos (\frac{\theta}{2}) \ket{0} + e^{i \phi} \sin (\frac{\theta}{2})\ket{1}$$
In [43]:
def qc_bloch(theta,phi):
    qc = QuantumCircuit(1,1) 
    qc.ry(theta,0)
    qc.rz(phi,0)
    return qc
  • .
